reviewText:
Product received for free

The concept of this game is quite appealing.  Don't let it fool you at all.  This game is far from what it appears to be.  This game is just another way for you to waste your money than realize you have truely wasted your money, putting money into this game is litterally like burning money.  Use that money for something more useful like oh I don't know getting a game that isn't filled with bad mechanic choices?

Okay if that above didn't stop you than hopefully this will.

I am a guy who plays games like Minecraft, Space Engineers, Age of Empires, recently Sins of a Solar Empire.  I have played World of Warcraft, Runescape, Evony, Evony2, Tera, MapleStory, Mabinogi.  If you don't think I got enough experience in this field than let me just say I spent around $400-$600 on WoW because of the subscription, faction transfers, race changes, server transfers, getting random crap from the shop such as the small pets and a mount or two.  I know what it is to waste money, back than though WoW was good to my standards.

This game though, this game I was going to actually throw some money into it, I was going to spend enough for half a year to a year subscription just to possibly get the boosts that seamed to be needed for staying decent in the game.

In all honesty it's not f2p unless you truely wish to torture yourself, no I haven't played it, I have read the reviews by those who have played it for a good 2,000 hours or so, ammount of time I probably spent in WoW. Let me list reasons it appealed to me and reasons for why I changed my mind:

-What appealed to me-
1. Sandbox elements {oh sweet I can jump in and slowly build myself an empire nice}
2. Hybrid style talent builds {oh sweet not too much restriction on a character, I like that, heck lets try being Tanky Priest lel}
3. Gathering Materials {oh so when building my empire it's like minecraft/age of empires where I gather the materials to build the homes and walls? NICE}
4. Don't need to keep the same skills? {Sweet if i get bored I can become an Archer priest or maybe a mage warlock combo with Dots galor? MMM yay destruction}


-What made me change my mind-
1. Finding out Labor isn't what I thought it was {Think about playing all those FB games you either still play or got sick of playing, that nice annoying energy bar that you ended up slowly wasting $50 on without even knowing it}
2. PvE? {apparently from the reviews the PvE isn't really there, sure you got quests but it doesn't seam that PvE is really there, you get bored after a long while being level cap}
3. Pay to Rek PvP? {So it's not just subscription based with a fake label but the PvP is pretty much pay to get the best gear because grinding will make you rage, and not provide you with what you need to survive agianst the rich little rekers}
4. Gear regrading or whatever {So ever play Elder Scrolls Oblivion, or ever play a game where you gotta constantly repair your gear?  Well apparently this game has that nice little mechanic, but makes it worse.  Apparently it degrades quicker than you can upgrade it, thus why this is Pay to Win PvP, aka Pay to play the side of the game that actually has content.  I've been on the side where I get rekt constantly because my gear isn't as good yet, I Don't feel like paying to be able to survive in PvP.}
5. Want to build an empire? {well get inline, apparently their isn't open land to build an empire, let alone expand it if you find an area.  Thus the sandbox aspect in all honesty is false and only for those who established at the very start of a new server.  Which I don't think new servers pop up much at all.}

In all truth this game has great potential, sadly that potential will never be attempted to be reached as this game has already been corrupted and the developers will never change such mechanics thus such a great idea has already been ruined by the greed of another developement company that thought of the worst choices to have an income.

So what I recommend you do, is keep looking and possibly find something that may not end up being as good of a concept as this but will be far better than playing a game you'll never have the money to really enjoy.
